##Ethereum
***
* A blockchain
* A single, canonical computer(EVM)




##Ether
***
* A cryptocurrency (a medium of exchange )
#### What is Ether
* the basic using example
    1. the only acceptable form of payment for transaction fees
    2. to validate and propose blocks on Mainnet.
    3. a primary form of collateral in the DeFi lending markets.
    4. a unit of account in NFT
* create decentralized applications (dapps)
    * depend on gas fees to stay safe  (limit the infinite use of EVM)

* Minting Ether
    * About 1/8 of the total issuance goes to the block proposer; the remainder is distributed across the other validators.
* Burning Ether
    * When users pay for their transactions, a base gas fee will be burned.
    * When network demand is high, blocks can burn more ether than they mint
        * effectively offsetting ether issuance.
* Denominations of ether
    * wei
    * gwei describe gas fee.
* Transferring Ether
    *  value filed ,specifies the amount of ether to be transferred
    * and it can pay for gas (smart contact)
